the way Pat put it about after you left!

52:05.709 --> 52:07.584
You take that back.

52:07.668 --> 52:11.626
- Aye, I'm sorry.
- You take a long hard look at yourself.

52:11.709 --> 52:15.126
I'm sorry, I'm not thinking straight.

52:15.293 --> 52:17.334
- Give me the tape.
- Okay.

52:20.626 --> 52:23.001
You're doing the right thing, Jeff.

52:25.584 --> 52:26.584
Truth time.

52:30.501 --> 52:34.251
'Mindhorn, the best detective
the Isle of Man had ever seen.'

52:34.918 --> 52:37.959
Out of the way! Coming through!

52:43.043 --> 52:45.543
Oh, God, no.

52:45.709 --> 52:47.126
Jasmine.

52:47.251 --> 52:48.418
I'm sorry.

52:48.543 --> 52:50.251
What for?

52:50.334 --> 52:51.918
Everything.

52:52.043 --> 52:54.043
You know about me and your mother

52:54.209 --> 52:56.626
- and who I am?
- Yes, yes, sadly I do.

52:56.709 --> 52:59.584
I want you to know I'm proud of you, Jas.

52:59.668 --> 53:01.209
- Can I call you Jas?
- No.

53:01.376 --> 53:04.043
Jasmine, I want us to get to know
each other really well.

53:04.209 --> 53:06.126
- This is weird.
- I know it's weird.

53:06.293 --> 53:08.293
I want us to set up regular phone calls.

53:08.418 --> 53:10.043
That's never going to happen.

53:10.126 --> 53:11.668
Okay, we'll go at your pace.

53:11.793 --> 53:16.709
Watch the news. You're going to see
your daddy blow the lid off this island.

53:24.376 --> 53:27.918
'So, to sum up, do we have a deal, then?'

53:28.043 --> 53:32.876
- I don't take very kindly to blackmail.
- 'All right, keep your wig on.'

53:34.001 --> 53:36.043
Okay, I'll see you there.

53:36.751 --> 53:40.084
- So the simpleton was filming us?
- Yeah, looks like it.

53:41.918 --> 53:46.334
I'm starting to think
framing Melly was a really bad idea.

53:46.459 --> 53:48.293
Get me Mindhorn!

53:48.418 --> 53:50.793
Mindhorn!

53:50.918 --> 53:53.543
Do you have a statement to make about this?

53:53.668 --> 53:57.959
'The Isle of Man is still one of the safest
and most tranquil tourist destinations.'

53:58.084 --> 53:59.084
Hello!

54:01.709 --> 54:05.293
Mindhorn's here!
I've got this, Chief. Stand your men down.

54:07.418 --> 54:09.001
'Is this the camera?

54:09.126 --> 54:11.376
'This man is innocent.

54:11.501 --> 54:14.001
'This tape will be the proof of my words.

54:15.043 --> 54:16.709
'You might want to swing a lens.'

54:16.793 --> 54:19.668
- Richard, what the hell are you doing?
- Trust me.

54:20.251 --> 54:23.834
Get one of your boffins to play this.
It shows that Melly's innocent.

54:23.959 --> 54:25.459
How do I look?

54:25.584 --> 54:27.376
Like you might need some help.

54:27.501 --> 54:29.626
Too late. I work alone.

54:31.334 --> 54:34.709
I'm coming, Melly,
Detective Mindhorn's on the case.

54:34.834 --> 54:36.334
Mindhorn!

54:39.834 --> 54:42.043
Shit, Jesus.

54:44.043 --> 54:45.668
Oh, God.

54:47.376 --> 54:49.001
Hiya, Mindhorn.

54:49.126 --> 54:50.876
Mindhorn?

54:51.001 --> 54:53.459
Is this still Operation
Apocalypse of Justice?

54:53.584 --> 54:55.501
I know you're innocent.

54:55.626 --> 54:57.709
This man is innocent. Play the tape.

54:57.834 --> 55:00.751
We'll play the tape at the station.

55:00.876 --> 55:03.668
No, I'm not going down the station.
Play the tape now.

55:03.751 --> 55:06.918
- Play it now.
- He's serious, Patricia.

55:07.043 --> 55:09.751
And so am I. Okay, people.

55:09.834 --> 55:12.626
Get ready to witness some truth bombs.

55:12.709 --> 55:16.001
'Ho, ho, ho!
You know how to do it, don't you?'

55:16.709 --> 55:17.501
What?

55:17.626 --> 55:19.751
'I'm gonna shit the truth out, bang!'

55:19.918 --> 55:23.084
- This is the wrong tape.
- 'My name is Bruce Mindhorn.'

55:23.251 --> 55:24.626
He swapped the tapes, okay?

55:24.709 --> 55:28.043
Jeff Moncrief, who I will kill,
has got the real tape.

55:28.251 --> 55:31.043
It's in the caravan.
We have to go to the caravan.

55:31.793 --> 55:34.001
We'll do that when you both come down.

55:34.709 --> 55:37.001
Richard, is Melly armed?

55:37.126 --> 55:39.084
No, no, no, negative.

55:39.251 --> 55:40.501
No, I have got a gun.

55:42.126 --> 55:44.126
This is not a gun, it's not real.

55:44.251 --> 55:46.709
- It is real.
- It's not real.

55:46.793 --> 55:48.751
- It's a toy.
- It's not a toy.

55:49.543 --> 55:50.834
See? Told you.

55:50.959 --> 55:52.251
- Go, man.
- Shoot.

55:54.084 --> 55:56.876
- Quick! This way, Mindhorn.
- This is not the way to go.

55:58.543 --> 56:00.751
- 'Call Equity!'
- What's the hoo-ha?

56:00.876 --> 56:04.251
- Thorncroft's gone insane.
- This is terrible.

56:04.376 --> 56:06.918
- Wait, did he sign that DVD thing?
- Yeah.

56:07.043 --> 56:08.543
In which case it's fantastic.

56:09.084 --> 56:10.709
Stop shooting.

56:10.876 --> 56:12.334
I haven't done anything.

56:12.418 --> 56:15.459
Stop making that stupid bird noise.

56:15.543 --> 56:16.834
Stop there.

56:18.001 --> 56:19.959
- Stop.
- They're heading into the mine.

56:21.709 --> 56:22.876
Stop right there.

56:34.834 --> 56:36.793
They've gone again, Chief.

56:36.959 --> 56:37.959
For now.

56:59.001 --> 57:01.293
DS Baines?

57:01.376 --> 57:03.251
Clever boy.

57:03.376 --> 57:05.501
You're coming with me.

57:06.376 --> 57:09.501
All I want to know is,
who else has seen this tape?

57:09.626 --> 57:13.501
Oh, no, no, no, no.
I can't reveal my sources.

57:13.626 --> 57:17.751
It was Richard Thorncroft.
This whole thing was his idea.

57:17.876 --> 57:20.543
- And possibly Pat Deville.
- Pat Deville?

57:20.709 --> 57:22.876
He picked it up from her house.

57:23.626 --> 57:25.293
How about 30 grand?

57:25.376 --> 57:26.918
Oh, Jeff.

57:27.584 --> 57:30.751
The last person who tried to blackmail me

57:30.876 --> 57:32.376
is on this tape.

57:32.501 --> 57:36.501
Only I haven't had
a torrid affair with you, Jeff.

57:36.626 --> 57:39.459
Let's call it 50 quid.
Then everybody's happy, eh?

57:43.293 --> 57:44.293
Oh, great.

57:44.418 --> 57:47.459
This isn't the Bronx,
this is the Isle of Man.

57:57.709 --> 58:00.334
- You okay, Mindhorn?
- Oh, God. I'm going to be sick.

58:00.459 --> 58:02.459
Come on, this way to safety.

58:02.584 --> 58:04.084
- Where are we going?
- The nest.

58:04.251 --> 58:07.209
It's lucky you're Special Forces.

58:08.626 --> 58:11.084
- How much further?
- It's just here.

58:12.584 --> 58:14.584
- What's this?
- You've got to jump.

58:14.709 --> 58:17.709
Oh, yeah. Yeah, let's just jump off a cliff!

58:17.834 --> 58:19.751
Yeah! You first.

58:19.876 --> 58:22.043
No!

58:30.043 --> 58:32.668
'It now seems certain
actor Richard Thorncroft,

58:32.751 --> 58:35.709
'who disappeared two days ago, is dead.

58:35.834 --> 58:37.543
'Thorncroft is the chief suspect

58:37.668 --> 58:40.876
'in the murder of Mindhorn PR guru,
Jeffrey Moncrief.

58:41.001 --> 58:45.209
'It is now accepted that Thorncroft could
be suffering a severe mental breakdown

58:45.334 --> 58:48.334
'after a long career lull
since the hit show ended.'

58:48.459 --> 58:51.209
'Even a short walk can take its toll
on the lower legs.

58:51.376 --> 58:53.459
'That's why I use Thrombi-Sox.'

58:53.584 --> 58:55.709
'Jeffrey Moncrief, who I will kill...'

58:56.709 --> 59:02.293
'You can never say it's a good thing
when someone is dead,

59:02.418 --> 59:07.668
'but maybe with Richard
this has been for the best.'

59:07.751 --> 59:12.126
'I keep expecting him
to walk through the door and say,

59:12.293 --> 59:15.334
""Hey, Pete, old buddy,
how are the DVD sales going?"

59:15.459 --> 59:20.126
'Because, of course, Mindhorn
is finally released today on DVD.

59:20.293 --> 59:21.376
'Yeah.

59:21.543 --> 59:24.584
'Actually, could you stop filming?
I think I'm about to cry.'

59:24.709 --> 59:29.293
'Time in the recording studio
yielded this album from 1990.

59:29.418 --> 59:32.543
'His signature tune,
"Can't Handcuff The Wind",

59:32.668 --> 59:36.001
'reached No.1
in several East European countries.'

59:47.668 --> 59:50.709
Oh, yeah. Oh, you're gonna love this.

59:51.293 --> 59:54.709
I've made you look exactly how you used to.

01:00:00.334 --> 01:00:02.543
Oh, it's perfect.

01:00:04.709 --> 01:00:06.959
- I can't move.
- I glued you into your clothes.

01:00:07.084 --> 01:00:09.834
There's three rolls of masking tape
around your neck.

01:00:09.959 --> 01:00:14.043
- You glued me into my clothes?
- Your hair came off in the sea.

01:00:14.209 --> 01:00:17.543
- But it's okay because I stuck it back on.
- I can't breathe.

01:00:17.668 --> 01:00:20.584
With superglue
so it will never come off again.

01:00:22.834 --> 01:00:24.084
Good, isn't it?

01:00:25.209 --> 01:00:27.209
And your eye patch.

01:00:27.334 --> 01:00:30.584
- Where are we?
- We are in an underground lair, the nest.

01:00:30.709 --> 01:00:33.876
And this is where we complete

01:00:34.001 --> 01:00:37.209
Operation Apocalypse of Justice.

01:00:37.334 --> 01:00:39.793
Right, first we need a penknife

01:00:39.918 --> 01:00:42.543
and this recorder belt.

01:00:42.668 --> 01:00:44.626
'Recorder belt.'

01:00:44.709 --> 01:00:46.751
Fake blood for fooling the baddies.

01:00:46.918 --> 01:00:49.584
And... a pretend gun.

01:00:50.459 --> 01:00:52.709
I'm your partner and we're working on a case.

01:00:52.793 --> 01:00:54.918
And it's a good case, isn't it, Mindhorn?

01:00:55.043 --> 01:00:57.501
Yeah, it's a really good case.

01:00:57.626 --> 01:01:01.126
Just one small problem is, I'm not Mindhorn.

01:01:01.293 --> 01:01:04.043
There is no Mindhorn. Mindhorn isn't real.

01:01:04.209 --> 01:01:06.126
It is real.

01:01:07.334 --> 01:01:09.876
- Truth powder.
- That is merchandise, okay?

01:01:10.001 --> 01:01:13.543
Do you know what merchandise is?
Cheap rubbish we sell to idiots.

01:01:13.668 --> 01:01:18.709
And by the way, that nearly blinded
four teenagers in Whitby in 1989.

01:01:18.793 --> 01:01:22.751
Mindhorn is a fictional character
in a show I did a quarter of a century ago.

01:01:23.501 --> 01:01:25.834
- What's a fictional character?
- I'm an actor.

01:01:25.918 --> 01:01:28.668
I used to be.
Now I just advertise orthopaedic socks.

01:01:28.751 --> 01:01:31.709
I don't even do that now
because John Nettle's got the gig!

01:01:32.334 --> 01:01:34.751
I don't... I don't understand.

01:01:34.918 --> 01:01:37.209
You don't understand? Let me clear things up.

01:01:37.334 --> 01:01:40.293
Your parents carked it,
you lost your marbles,

01:01:40.418 --> 01:01:43.543
you got fixated with me
in some weird, creepy way

01:01:43.626 --> 01:01:45.001
I don't want to get into,

01:01:45.126 --> 01:01:49.293
you think I'm here to rescue you
but I am a self-obsessed arsehole.

01:01:49.459 --> 01:01:50.793
Does that clear things up?

01:01:50.876 --> 01:01:54.501
'Paul Melly, wanted in connection
with the murder of Katya Lipinskii,

01:01:54.668 --> 01:01:56.084
'is also presumed dead.

01:01:56.251 --> 01:01:59.459
'Melly, 32, is believed
to have a mental age of nine.'

01:01:59.584 --> 01:02:01.293
Who's going to clear my name?

01:02:01.376 --> 01:02:02.376
Nobody.

01:02:03.751 --> 01:02:05.251
There's no evidence.

01:02:05.376 --> 01:02:07.793
We had a tape. The tape's gone. It's over.

01:02:10.126 --> 01:02:12.126
Both of them?

01:02:13.084 --> 01:02:14.668
Both of them?

01:02:14.751 --> 01:02:17.376
- What do you mean, both of them?
- I made a copy.

01:02:18.126 --> 01:02:21.084
You taught me that. Always make a copy.

01:02:21.251 --> 01:02:25.126
Well, Mindhorn did, only you're not Mindhorn.

01:02:25.293 --> 01:02:26.501
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

01:02:26.626 --> 01:02:28.043
I am Mindhorn.

01:02:28.709 --> 01:02:31.668
- What? But you said...
- You passed the test.

01:02:31.751 --> 01:02:33.251
Kestrel, well done.

01:02:34.293 --> 01:02:36.209
- Did I?
- You made promotion, partner.

01:02:36.376 --> 01:02:39.793
From now on you shall be known as the Falcon.

01:02:39.876 --> 01:02:41.376
No, I prefer Kestrel.

01:02:41.543 --> 01:02:43.293
Kestrel's fine. Where's the tape?

01:02:43.418 --> 01:02:47.084
I made a copy of the tape and
put it in your car at Mindhorn Heights.

01:02:47.209 --> 01:02:48.209
Yes!

01:02:48.293 --> 01:02:51.918
I'm going to pack the bag
for the finale when we kill the baddies.

01:02:52.043 --> 01:02:55.709
Sounds like a plan, partner.
I'll give you a signal when I need you.

01:02:55.834 --> 01:02:57.876
- What's the signal?
- You'll hear it.

01:02:58.001 --> 01:03:00.584
I need to hear it now.

01:03:00.709 --> 01:03:02.668
No.

01:03:02.751 --> 01:03:04.459
- Better.
- Good, okay.

01:03:04.584 --> 01:03:06.876
- Here, make sure you wear it.
- What is that?

01:03:06.959 --> 01:03:09.376
- It's a recorder belt.
- Recorder belt, okay.

01:03:09.501 --> 01:03:11.626
- Strapping that on now.
- And this.

01:03:11.751 --> 01:03:13.793
Roger that. Weird plastic radio. Got it.

01:03:13.918 --> 01:03:16.751
- Er, does this work?
- No.

01:03:16.918 --> 01:03:19.751
- It does work, actually, FYI.
- Oh, right.

01:03:22.418 --> 01:03:23.918
Who are you calling?

01:03:24.043 --> 01:03:25.793
The only person we can trust.

01:03:36.418 --> 01:03:38.418
- Baines.
- Richard, wow!

01:03:38.543 --> 01:03:40.043
- Don't ask.
- You're alive.

01:03:40.209 --> 01:03:41.751
- Where's Melly?
- In a cave.

01:03:41.918 --> 01:03:43.543
He hid a copy of the tape at Pat's.

01:03:44.376 --> 01:03:45.418
Whereabouts?

01:03:45.501 --> 01:03:48.626
In the garage, in the glove compartment
of the Mindhorn car.

01:03:49.918 --> 01:03:53.084
- What have you got the gun for?
- You know too much, Richard.

01:03:54.043 --> 01:03:57.126
I don't know anything.
I'm actually quite confused.

01:03:57.293 --> 01:04:01.084
- You know that I killed Moncrief, right?
- I did not know that.

01:04:01.209 --> 01:04:04.126
- Well, you do now.
- Not a problem. I can blank it out.

01:04:04.251 --> 01:04:07.418
I have that capacity.
I've blanked out huge chapters of my life.

01:04:07.543 --> 01:04:10.209
- This is just one more thing.
- Sorry, Richard.

01:04:10.334 --> 01:04:11.334
Final curtain.

01:04:20.876 --> 01:04:22.668
Truth powder.

01:04:24.834 --> 01:04:26.459
- Quick, the gun.
- What is that?

01:04:26.584 --> 01:04:27.668
Come on!

01:04:29.293 --> 01:04:32.709
- Jesus Christ!
- She's left the keys in the bike.

01:04:34.418 --> 01:04:35.918
Yes!

01:04:36.084 --> 01:04:37.584
Why did you do that?

01:04:37.668 --> 01:04:41.209
We could have used the bike
to get away, you stupid berk!

01:04:51.251 --> 01:04:54.334
- Hello.
- 'Hi, Pat, it's DS Baines here.'

01:04:54.459 --> 01:04:57.584
I just thought I should tell you
that Richard is alive.

01:04:58.793 --> 01:05:01.959
- He's alive?
- 'Alive, yeah, yeah. Great news.'

01:05:02.126 --> 01:05:05.293
Um, mixed bag, though. He is delusional.

01:05:05.418 --> 01:05:07.459
Oh, God, he's seriously ill, isn't he?

01:05:07.584 --> 01:05:10.084
'He is, he is. He's on his way to you now.

01:05:10.251 --> 01:05:12.709
'He thinks he's in an old episode of Mindhorn

01:05:12.793 --> 01:05:15.251
'and I need you to keep him there

01:05:15.376 --> 01:05:18.626
'and I will come to you, okay,
so just wait there.'

01:05:22.501 --> 01:05:24.084
Where's the car?

01:05:25.668 --> 01:05:27.459
Oh, where is it?

01:05:27.584 --> 01:05:29.918
Where's the bloody car?

01:05:30.043 --> 01:05:32.209
It should be here.

01:05:45.293 --> 01:05:46.334
Richard?

01:05:48.334 --> 01:05:49.501
Are you okay?

01:05:53.293 --> 01:05:54.293
No.

01:05:54.418 --> 01:05:57.709
I'm having a really bad day. Where's my car?

01:05:57.793 --> 01:05:59.876
Why don't you just come and sit down?

01:06:00.001 --> 01:06:02.209
I can't sit down. I'm glued in.

01:06:02.334 --> 01:06:03.876
Just calm down and...

01:06:04.001 --> 01:06:05.751
Baines is trying to kill me.

01:06:05.876 --> 01:06:08.668
She's corrupt. There's a bald man.

01:06:08.793 --> 01:06:12.084
He's... he's got cats on his shoes.
I've seen them.

01:06:12.251 --> 01:06:15.043
Not real cats, false cats,
tiny false cats on his shoes.

01:06:15.209 --> 01:06:17.126
Richard, none of this is real.

01:06:17.293 --> 01:06:19.876
It's all real, it's come real.

01:06:20.001 --> 01:06:21.671
Where's my car? Where's it gone?

01:06:21.751 --> 01:06:26.834
The car? Clive is bringing the car.
It will be here in a few minutes.

01:06:26.918 --> 01:06:30.084
Now, just calm down and talk to me.

01:06:30.251 --> 01:06:33.418
- They're coming. I can't wait.
- Let's talk about us.

01:06:33.543 --> 01:06:34.626
There is no us.

01:06:34.709 --> 01:06:38.418
I blew it. I walked out.
The only thing that ever meant anything.

01:06:38.501 --> 01:06:39.834
You.

01:06:40.959 --> 01:06:45.334
Since I left you,
my life has been... really quite bad.

01:06:45.459 --> 01:06:48.793
Richard, it's all right. It's all right.

01:06:48.876 --> 01:06:51.918
Leaving you was
the biggest mistake of my life.

01:06:54.334 --> 01:06:55.751
What is that?

01:06:56.584 --> 01:06:57.584
The Kestrel.

01:06:58.793 --> 01:07:01.751
Sorry, I'm so sorry.

01:07:05.418 --> 01:07:09.043
So he's not dead,
he just fell asleep on the sunbed.

01:07:09.251 --> 01:07:10.959
Put down the gardening equipment.

01:07:11.084 --> 01:07:16.459
Get out of my house before I strim
that stupid fucking wig off.

01:07:16.626 --> 01:07:20.126
Where's my car?

01:07:20.293 --> 01:07:21.959
Don't tell him, Clive.

01:07:23.043 --> 01:07:26.626
- Pete took it for the parade.
- What's going on?

01:07:26.709 --> 01:07:28.543
Stay away. His brain's come loose.

01:07:28.668 --> 01:07:30.668
Whatever happens next,

01:07:30.751 --> 01:07:32.709
I want you to remember two things.

01:07:32.793 --> 01:07:34.543
One, I'm innocent.

01:07:35.584 --> 01:07:36.918
And two,

01:07:37.876 --> 01:07:39.334
Daddy loves you.

01:07:45.418 --> 01:07:47.459
Oh, shit. Oh, no. Oh, dear.

01:07:47.584 --> 01:07:50.709
These are nothing to do with me.
Dirty, dirty Richard.

01:07:50.876 --> 01:07:53.918
- You're pathetic.
- These aren't mine.

01:07:54.084 --> 01:07:55.501
What are all these?

01:07:55.584 --> 01:07:57.876
They're from my pen pal in France.

01:08:02.668 --> 01:08:04.584
These are all from Richard.

01:08:04.709 --> 01:08:06.543
I was trying to protect you, Pat.

01:08:08.084 --> 01:08:09.751
The man is poison.

01:08:11.709 --> 01:08:13.209
I'm going to work.

01:08:18.584 --> 01:08:22.251
- There she blows.
- And a load of fake Mindhorns.

01:08:27.542 --> 01:08:30.876
I really do think this could be
the best Manx Day we've ever had.

01:08:30.959 --> 01:08:34.334
- Sorry I'm late.
- Better late than never.

01:08:35.834 --> 01:08:40.001
I'll be making my speech
slightly later than scheduled.

01:08:40.126 --> 01:08:43.084
Um, I provided copies for you all.

01:08:43.251 --> 01:08:46.126
They're on the table in the entrance hall.

01:08:46.292 --> 01:08:49.792
Thanks, everyone. Go and join the madness.

01:08:49.917 --> 01:08:51.251
All right?

01:08:51.417 --> 01:08:52.959
Okay, thanks.

01:08:56.126 --> 01:08:58.126
Pat, could I have a word?

01:09:11.334 --> 01:09:13.084
Pat, Pat, Pat, Pat, Pat, Pat...

01:09:14.751 --> 01:09:17.584
You know, don't you?

01:09:22.709 --> 01:09:25.459
I'm in a bit of a pickle, aren't I?

01:09:25.584 --> 01:09:29.251
I mean, you're a journalist,
you're not going to keep it to yourself,

01:09:29.334 --> 01:09:30.917
something this big.

01:09:31.792 --> 01:09:34.667
How can I let you leave this room?

01:09:34.751 --> 01:09:39.459
I absolutely cannot have people
finding out that I am bald.

01:09:46.917 --> 01:09:50.001
I think bald men are sexy.

01:09:51.876 --> 01:09:53.084
I think you're right.

01:09:53.209 --> 01:09:56.709
Oh, I'll have to take this.

01:09:57.751 --> 01:10:01.293
'The tape's in the parade.
I'm going after them.'

01:10:03.918 --> 01:10:05.751
She knows.

01:10:12.418 --> 01:10:16.626
Welcome, one and all, to the Manx Day parade.

01:10:16.751 --> 01:10:19.293
We're going to have some great fun.

01:10:19.418 --> 01:10:21.418
Thank you.

01:10:22.001 --> 01:10:26.084
I wonder who's going to win
today's Float of the Year competition.

01:10:26.251 --> 01:10:29.001
Could it be the really big spider,

01:10:29.126 --> 01:10:32.251
or the two massive papier-mâché heads?

01:10:32.418 --> 01:10:35.626
Or perhaps the crazy caterpillar,
runner-up last year?

01:10:35.709 --> 01:10:38.959
Fingers crossed for no more trapped ankles.

01:10:39.043 --> 01:10:43.709
And there's Trevor
in his intergalactic mobility scooter.

01:10:44.251 --> 01:10:48.126
The Windjammer float there, always good fun.

01:10:48.293 --> 01:10:52.626
It's the most successful TV programme
ever made on the Isle of Man.

01:10:52.709 --> 01:10:55.709
Oh, and look, it's the villain,

01:10:55.793 --> 01:10:59.084
but Windjammer disarms him and saves the day.

01:10:59.251 --> 01:11:00.834
Super stuff.

01:11:00.918 --> 01:11:04.543
And, new this year, the Mindhorn contingent.

01:11:04.709 --> 01:11:06.876
Remember Mindhorn, folks?

01:11:07.001 --> 01:11:10.876
Mindhorn, of course,
originally played by, um...

01:11:11.001 --> 01:11:14.001
Oh, and who's this? Another Mindhorn.

01:11:14.126 --> 01:11:18.251
And a crazy person, a sort of chicken man.

01:11:26.293 --> 01:11:29.876
I don't remember the episode,
"Mindhorn and the Chicken Man".

01:11:30.001 --> 01:11:32.543
What's Mindhorn doing now?

01:11:32.668 --> 01:11:38.126
No doubt finding some crucial piece
of evidence to uncover the truth.

01:11:39.251 --> 01:11:43.293
And here comes the baddie. Oh, no!

01:11:46.626 --> 01:11:48.001
Wonderful lookalike.

01:11:48.126 --> 01:11:53.293
Doesn't she look like Manx TV's
very own Pat Deville?

01:11:55.584 --> 01:11:57.668
- Go, go, go!
- I can't make it go.

01:11:57.793 --> 01:12:00.584
I knew you hadn't passed your test,
you naughty liar.

01:12:01.084 --> 01:12:05.834
You can take my woman,
but you can't take my fucking car.

01:12:05.959 --> 01:12:07.709
- It won't go.
- The handbrake's on.

01:12:07.834 --> 01:12:09.084
Where's the handbrake?

01:12:09.293 --> 01:12:11.001
- There!
- Like a Formula 1 champion!

01:12:12.293 --> 01:12:14.918
Oh, shit!

01:12:15.959 --> 01:12:19.709
Fantastic! Full marks to the stuntman.

01:12:19.834 --> 01:12:22.334
- I wasn't ready.
- I can't actually drive.

01:12:22.459 --> 01:12:23.959
- Get out!
- I never learned.

01:12:24.084 --> 01:12:26.251
- Oh, shut up!
- Never had to.

01:12:26.334 --> 01:12:28.876
I was driven everywhere
so I didn't have to bother.

01:12:29.043 --> 01:12:30.501
Hi, yep, hello.

01:12:32.918 --> 01:12:36.209
And here's the baddie retrieving her gun.

01:12:36.376 --> 01:12:38.584
- Get in the car!
- What?

01:12:38.709 --> 01:12:40.793
- Oh!
- Classic!

01:12:43.043 --> 01:12:45.876
And now for the nail-biting finale...

01:12:48.709 --> 01:12:51.043
Oh, bad luck, baddie.

01:12:51.209 --> 01:12:54.293
And that's Mindhorn,
winner of the day in my view.

01:12:55.418 --> 01:12:56.751
Great stuff!

01:13:02.251 --> 01:13:05.876
We're flying to the truth!

01:13:22.834 --> 01:13:27.001
What are we doing? It's a dead-end.
Where are we?

01:13:28.126 --> 01:13:30.376
- This is your cove, Mindhorn.
- What?

01:13:30.543 --> 01:13:33.709
- Where do we go from here?
- Well, the tunnels!

01:13:34.751 --> 01:13:36.251
- Melly.
- Melly, come on.

01:13:41.126 --> 01:13:43.001
What's wrong?

01:13:44.043 --> 01:13:47.001
That was... That was great, wasn't it?

01:13:48.251 --> 01:13:50.001
You've been shot.

01:13:50.126 --> 01:13:52.543
- You're bleeding.
- No, no, no. Don't worry.

01:13:52.668 --> 01:13:54.918
It's fake blood.

01:13:55.043 --> 01:13:58.376
- Oh, no, that's there.
- We have to get you some help.

01:13:59.001 --> 01:14:01.834
- I'm dying, Mindhorn.
- No, no, you're not.

01:14:01.959 --> 01:14:03.709
- This is the end.
- No.

01:14:03.876 --> 01:14:07.626
- Go on without me. Leave me here.
- I'm not leaving you.

01:14:09.793 --> 01:14:11.709
Because I'm a good partner?

01:14:11.793 --> 01:14:15.459
You're the best damn partner
a man could ask for, Kestrel.

01:14:15.584 --> 01:14:17.751
Your parents would be proud of you.

01:14:17.834 --> 01:14:19.626
I'm proud of you.

01:14:20.876 --> 01:14:22.459
Thanks, Mindhorn.

01:14:23.668 --> 01:14:26.334
It's been an honour to be your partner.

01:14:27.834 --> 01:14:30.668
Well, it's the best 15 minutes of my life.

01:14:32.668 --> 01:14:35.793
Here's a copy of the tape. Now, go.

01:14:35.918 --> 01:14:40.209
Promise me you'll clear my name, Mindhorn.

01:14:40.793 --> 01:14:43.126
- I promise.
- And promise me...

01:14:43.293 --> 01:14:46.459
you two will finally get it together.

01:14:46.626 --> 01:14:49.459
- Mm-hm.
- I'm sorry, I can't promise you that.

01:14:49.584 --> 01:14:52.251
I mean... yes.

01:14:53.043 --> 01:14:55.293
Give him a kiss, Angela.

01:15:04.001 --> 01:15:07.084
One last thing, Mindhorn.

01:15:07.251 --> 01:15:11.293
Tell me the truth about Richard Thorncroft.

01:15:12.709 --> 01:15:14.793
Who is he?

01:15:16.834 --> 01:15:19.834
Let's just say, he's someone I used to know.

01:15:19.959 --> 01:15:21.834
Right, that's...

01:15:31.543 --> 01:15:33.793
You poor deluded fool.

01:15:35.418 --> 01:15:38.084
I am Richard Thorncroft.

01:15:50.251 --> 01:15:52.959
At least he didn't die in vain.

01:15:55.126 --> 01:15:56.793
What the hell is this?

01:15:59.834 --> 01:16:01.918
Yep, it's Plasticine.

01:16:03.209 --> 01:16:06.209
Yep, it's a Plasticine copy.

01:16:06.334 --> 01:16:09.376
Ha-ha! It's Plasticine!

01:16:20.793 --> 01:16:23.043
- Pat!
- Quick.

01:16:46.126 --> 01:16:48.668
'It's time for the apocalypse of justice.'

01:17:01.084 --> 01:17:02.709
Baines, don't shoot.

01:17:04.334 --> 01:17:08.543
We've got the tape. Richard has it.
It's safe. I'll take you to him.

01:17:08.626 --> 01:17:12.293
Maybe we can strike a deal. I don't want
to see the mayor go down any more...

01:17:12.459 --> 01:17:15.209
Jesus, Pat! Is that the best you can do?

01:17:15.334 --> 01:17:18.668
- I thought you were a good actress.
- She's good enough.

01:17:19.334 --> 01:17:21.001
Lose the piece.

01:17:24.376 --> 01:17:26.293
Turn around, slowly.

01:17:27.543 --> 01:17:29.251
Hands in the air.

01:17:30.959 --> 01:17:32.793
Now who's holding all the aces?

01:17:32.918 --> 01:17:34.709
- Aargh!
- Me, I think.

01:17:34.834 --> 01:17:38.459
- Richard, you bloody idiot!
- I didn't know she was going to do that.

01:17:40.543 --> 01:17:42.793
No! Patricia!

01:17:44.209 --> 01:17:45.751
Patricia, Patricia.

01:17:45.876 --> 01:17:47.334
Richard.

01:17:47.459 --> 01:17:50.293
- I'm so sorry.
- No, I'm sorry.

01:17:51.043 --> 01:17:54.626
- I never knew you wrote me those letters.
- Shh, that doesn't matter now.

01:17:54.709 --> 01:17:57.668
- Clive hid them from me.
- What a wanker.

01:17:58.793 --> 01:18:00.834
I'm sorry that I never believed you.

01:18:00.959 --> 01:18:02.751
And I'm sorry.

01:18:04.376 --> 01:18:06.918
I love you, Richard.

01:18:13.584 --> 01:18:16.668
Fucking hell. Where's the tape, Richard?

01:18:18.793 --> 01:18:20.501
There is no tape.

01:18:21.126 --> 01:18:24.668
It's fake, like everything else in my life!

01:18:25.709 --> 01:18:28.209
Without her, I may as well be dead.

01:18:29.709 --> 01:18:31.876
That was just a figure of speech.

01:18:34.709 --> 01:18:35.959
Why?

01:18:37.209 --> 01:18:39.001
Why?

01:18:40.584 --> 01:18:44.543
The Mayor's my uncle,
so I've got to clean up his mess.

01:18:44.668 --> 01:18:46.543
Family's family.

01:18:47.876 --> 01:18:50.459
- My family runs Man.
- Call an ambulance.

01:18:51.418 --> 01:18:53.709
It's not too late. I can forget.

01:18:53.793 --> 01:18:57.084
- What, that I killed Moncrief?
- Yeah, that.

01:19:00.793 --> 01:19:03.084
I can pretend I don't know that.

01:19:03.209 --> 01:19:06.376
- I can pretend!
- You're not that good an actor.

01:19:13.543 --> 01:19:16.334
Baines, are you all right?

01:19:16.459 --> 01:19:18.251
He shot Pat.

01:19:19.126 --> 01:19:23.251
He killed her and
then he tried to kill me and I...

01:19:23.376 --> 01:19:27.126
I had to take him down.
I had to take him down!

01:19:30.959 --> 01:19:32.501
- Baines.
- Chief.

01:19:32.626 --> 01:19:34.834
There was nothing I could do, it was, er...

01:19:34.959 --> 01:19:36.959
There was nothing I could do.

01:19:40.418 --> 01:19:42.043
Nice working with you again.

01:19:42.918 --> 01:19:45.376
What's going on, Thorncroft?

01:19:45.543 --> 01:19:47.876
'The Mayor's my uncle,
so I've got to clean up his mess.'

01:19:47.959 --> 01:19:49.209
'I can forget.'

01:19:49.334 --> 01:19:52.418
'What, that I killed Moncrief?
You're not that good an actor.'

01:19:52.543 --> 01:19:54.543
Aren't I?

01:19:56.626 --> 01:19:57.751
Mum!

01:19:57.876 --> 01:19:59.543
- Jasmine!
- Not cool.

01:19:59.668 --> 01:20:02.959
- Both sets of keys, give them to me.
- Think about what you're doing, Baines.

01:20:03.084 --> 01:20:04.876
Keys now or I'll blow her away.

01:20:05.001 --> 01:20:07.751
Get your filthy hands off my daughter!

01:20:09.126 --> 01:20:12.876
She's not your daughter,
she's Windjammer's daughter.

01:20:14.293 --> 01:20:17.834
- Clive, do something.
- I'm not wearing appropriate footwear.

01:20:17.959 --> 01:20:21.334
Stand down, Clive.
It's time I did my own stunts.

01:20:28.793 --> 01:20:30.668
It's Ginga time.

01:20:46.001 --> 01:20:50.126
This is the Ginga.

01:21:01.084 --> 01:21:05.501
I'm moving between the air.

01:21:12.709 --> 01:21:14.459
I'm here.

01:21:16.876 --> 01:21:20.334
I'm the bringer of the Ginga.

01:21:23.334 --> 01:21:25.418
And that's Capoeira.

01:21:29.251 --> 01:21:30.584
Jas.

01:21:32.626 --> 01:21:34.251
Ah, the Mayor was her uncle.

01:21:34.376 --> 01:21:37.834
Seems I was right
about the limited gene pool.

01:21:38.001 --> 01:21:40.543
I'm sorry that I rode you so hard back then.

01:21:40.668 --> 01:21:43.084
I hope we can put our differences behind us.

01:21:43.293 --> 01:21:45.959
I will if you will, and if it helps at all,

01:21:46.084 --> 01:21:49.709
I was pretty wasted, I don't even
remember that night with your wife.

01:21:49.793 --> 01:21:52.751
- What night with my wife?
- That's the spirit.

01:21:53.751 --> 01:21:57.751
My God, Richard. That was so brave.
It's a miracle you weren't shot.

01:21:57.876 --> 01:22:00.209
Ah, no more lies. I have to be honest.

01:22:00.293 --> 01:22:02.751
The truth is, I knew
there were blanks in that gun.

01:22:02.876 --> 01:22:06.293
No, no, this was Baines' gun.
That was live ammunition.

01:22:09.834 --> 01:22:11.209
Richard?

01:22:12.543 --> 01:22:13.918
I've got you.

01:22:14.626 --> 01:22:16.418
You got me all right.

01:22:17.626 --> 01:22:20.084
